mySecurityMIB.name: mySecurityMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

mySecurityMIB.description: This module defines my security mibs.

myEnableSnmpAgent.name: myEnableSnmpAgent
myEnableSnmpAgent.description: Enabled indicate that user can manage switch by snmp agent, disabled indicate that user can't manage switch by snmp agent.

myEnableWeb.name: myEnableWeb
myEnableWeb.description: Enabled indicate that user can manage switch by web, disabled indicate that user can't manage switch by web.

myEnableTelnet.name: myEnableTelnet
myEnableTelnet.description: Enabled indicate that user can manage switch by telnet, disabled indicate that user can't manage switch by telnet.

myTelnetHostIpTable.name: myTelnetHostIpTable
myTelnetHostIpTable.description: The table of telnet client's IP address, only these hostes can access the telnet server.

myTelnetHostIpEntry.name: myTelnetHostIpEntry
myTelnetHostIpEntry.description: The entry of telnet host IP address table.

myTelnetHostIpAddress.name: myTelnetHostIpAddress
myTelnetHostIpAddress.description: The telnet client's IP address, Only these hostes can access the telnet server

myTelnetHostIpEnable.name: myTelnetHostIpEnable
myTelnetHostIpEnable.description: The telnet client's IP address enable state

myWebHostIpTable.name: myWebHostIpTable
myWebHostIpTable.description: The table of web client's IP address, only these hostes can access the web server.

myWebHostIpEntry.name: myWebHostIpEntry
myWebHostIpEntry.description: The entry of web host IP address table.

myWebHostIpAddress.name: myWebHostIpAddress
myWebHostIpAddress.description: The web client's IP address, Only these hostes can access the web server

myWebHostIpEnable.name: myWebHostIpEnable
myWebHostIpEnable.description: The web client's IP address enable state

mySecurityAddressEntry.name: mySecurityAddressEntry
mySecurityAddressEntry.description: The entry of Security address table.

mySecurityAddressFdbId.name: mySecurityAddressFdbId
mySecurityAddressFdbId.description: The VID of vlan which the security address blongs to.

mySecurityAddressAddress.name: mySecurityAddressAddress
mySecurityAddressAddress.description: The MAC address of the security address.

mySecurityAddressPort.name: mySecurityAddressPort
mySecurityAddressPort.description: The interface which the security address blongs to.

mySecurityAddressIpAddr.name: mySecurityAddressIpAddr
mySecurityAddressIpAddr.description: The IP address which the security address bind.It's meaning only when mySecurityAddressIfBindIp is true.

mySecurityAddressIfBindIp.name: mySecurityAddressIfBindIp
mySecurityAddressIfBindIp.description: this object offer the means whether security address will bind IP.

mySecurityAddressRemainAge.name: mySecurityAddressRemainAge
mySecurityAddressRemainAge.description: The remain age of the security address, in units of minute.

mySecurityAddressType.name: mySecurityAddressType
mySecurityAddressType.description: The type of the security address

mySecurityAddressStatus.name: mySecurityAddressStatus
mySecurityAddressStatus.description: entry status of this entry. and the means in this enviraments can reffer to the text-convention definition of the RowStatus.

myBindAddressTable.name: myBindAddressTable
myBindAddressTable.description: IP-MAC bind table. The source MAC address must be bound when the switch receives the frame with source IP address defined in this table. Otherwise, the frame will be discarded.

myBindAddressEntry.name: myBindAddressEntry
myBindAddressEntry.description: The entry of Bind address table.

myBindAddressIpAddr.name: myBindAddressIpAddr
myBindAddressIpAddr.description: The IP address which the security address bind.It's meaning only when myBindAddressIfBindIp is true.

myBindMacAddress.name: myBindMacAddress
myBindMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the security address.

myBindAddressStatus.name: myBindAddressStatus
myBindAddressStatus.description: entry status. Setting this value to 'invalid' will remove this entry

myPortSecurityTable.name: myPortSecurityTable
myPortSecurityTable.description: list of port security configuration objects.

myPortSecurViolationType.name: myPortSecurViolationType
myPortSecurViolationType.description: this object define 3 grades of port security: violation-protect(1): normal security grade, indicate that when the a datagram received on a port with illegal MAC address will be discarded but not send trap, legal and illegal MAC to a port security is defined by per port's security below. violation-restrict(2): normal security grade, indicate that when the a datagram received on a port with illegal MAC address will be discarded and send trap, legal and illegal MAC to a port security is defined by per port's security below. violation-shutdown(3): strict security grade, indicate that when the a datagram received on a port with illegal MAC address, the port will be disabled for the violation of the port's security and send trap.

myPortSecurityAddrNum.name: myPortSecurityAddrNum
myPortSecurityAddrNum.description: This value means the address number threshold of this port. A new address want to add to the port address will be refused when address num exceed this value. This value is valid when myPortSecurityStatus is 'disabled'

myPortSecurityAddrAge.name: myPortSecurityAddrAge
myPortSecurityAddrAge.description: Aging time in units of minute of security address of interface

myPortStaticSecurAddrIfAge.name: myPortStaticSecurAddrIfAge
myPortStaticSecurAddrIfAge.description: This object offer the means whether enable static configured security address aging.

myPortSecurityAddressCurrentNum.name: myPortSecurityAddressCurrentNum
myPortSecurityAddressCurrentNum.description: Current number of the security address of interface.

myPortStaticSecurAddrCurrentNum.name: myPortStaticSecurAddrCurrentNum
myPortStaticSecurAddrCurrentNum.description: Current number of the static configured security address of interface.

myPortSecurityIpDistrMode.name: myPortSecurityIpDistrMode
myPortSecurityIpDistrMode.description: IP Distrute Mode (0:Static-only mode, 1:Dynamic-only mode, 2:Dynamic and Static mode, 3:Unspecified mode)

portSecurityViolate.name: portSecurityViolate
portSecurityViolate.description: the mac lock violate trap indicates that if you have set the threshold number of learned addresses from a port, and their comes a new address from the port, but the addresses for the port is already full.

mySecurityMIBCompliance.name: mySecurityMIBCompliance
mySecurityMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the My Security MIB

myUserManageMIBGroup.name: myUserManageMIBGroup
myUserManageMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing status snmp and web and telnet management agent to a My agent.

mySecurityAddressMIBGroup.name: mySecurityAddressMIBGroup
mySecurityAddressMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing security address to a My agent.

myPortSecurityMIBGroup.name: myPortSecurityMIBGroup
myPortSecurityMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing port security to a My agent.
